function Start(idActorDamager, idActorDamaged)
	
-- Evil monster convo about disturbing his slumber.	
	Hydra.ActorPlayConversation(S_CONVO_INTRO, idActorDamager, idActorDamaged) 
	Hydra.QActorAnimAndNewIdle(idActorDamaged, S_ANIM_WELL_RUPTURE, S_ANIM_WELL_IDLE)

end

function Start(flTimeRemaining)

-- Additional VFX of bats emerging from the blood rupture
	Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroup(idSelf,S_EG_BAT_FOUNTAIN_PHASE1)
	Hydra.QActorAnim(ID_WELL_GIZMO, S_ANIM_WELL_RUPTURE)

-- Start the second round of spawners
	for i, idPhase02 in ipairs(tPhase02Spawners) do
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idPhase02) then
			Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idPhase02, false)
		end
	end


end

function Start(flTimeRemaining)

	local idConversationPlayer = Hydra.ActorGetClosestPlayer(ID_WELL_GIZMO)
	Hydra.ActorPlayConversation(S_CONVO_PHASE_2_INTRO, idConversationPlayer, ID_WELL_GIZMO) 

end

function Start()

-- If the player achieves the bonus start the final baddie conversation
-- If no bonus destroy the rupture
	if bBonusAchieved == true then
		local idConversationPlayer = Hydra.ActorGetClosestPlayer(ID_WELL_GIZMO)
		Hydra.ActorPlayConversation(S_CONVO_PHASE_3_INTRO, idConversationPlayer, ID_WELL_GIZMO) 
	else
		Hydra.ActorKill(ID_WELL_GIZMO)
		Hydra.ActorKill(idSuperElite) --killing the spawn gizmo here to fix bug FEN-605225, when this gizmo doesn't trigger it never cleans up, so you can't complete the Event because it is still in the ActorGroup
	end

end

function Start(idActorNPC, sConversation, idActorPlayer)

-- After the final baddie conversation destroy the rupture and spawn him
	Hydra.ActorKill(ID_WELL_GIZMO)
	Hydra.Wait(0.5)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idSuperElite, false)

end

function Start(idActorSpawned, idActorSpawner)

-- Buffing the bats to make them a little more than just a 1 hit kill
	Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(S_BAT_BUFF, "DAMAGE_RESISTANCE", idActorSpawned)
	
-- Set the variable that allows their AI to start merging immediately	
	Hydra.ActorSetAILocalVariable(idActorSpawned, "CAN_FORM", 1)

end
